{{Infobox noble | name = Usatsuhiko no Mikoto (菟狭津彦命) | image = | image_size = | caption = | era = [[Ancient Japan|Ancient]], [[Yayoi period]] | birth_date = Unknown | death_date = Unknown | other_names = Usatsuhiko, Usatsuhiko no Mikoto | titles = First [[Usa no Kuni no Miyatsuko]] | allegiance = [[Emperor Jimmu]] | clan = [[Usa clan]] | parents = [[Ame-no-Mikuhari-no-Mikoto]] | siblings = [[Usatsuhime]] | spouse = | children = Tsunetsuhiko no Mikoto }}
'''Usatsuhiko no Mikoto''' (菟狭津彦命, birth and death unknown) was an ancient Japanese noble and the first '''[[Usa no Kuni no Miyatsuko]]'''.
== Overview == In the '''''[[Kojiki]]''''', he is referred to as '''Usatsuhiko''', while the '''''[[Nihon Shoki]]''''' and ''[[Kōshon Honki]]'' use '''菟狭津彦''', and the ''Kuni no Miyatsuko Honki'' records his name as '''Usatsuhiko no Mikoto'''.
The '''''Kojiki''''' describes him as residing in [[Usa District]], [[Toyokuni Province]], while the '''''Nihon Shoki''''' situates him in Usa, [[Chikushi Province]]. He is mentioned alongside his sister, [[Usatsuhime]].
According to the '''''Nihon Shoki''''', when [[Emperor Jimmu]] landed in Usa during his [[Jimmu's eastern expedition|eastward expedition]], he was met by Usatsuhiko and [[Usatsuhime]]. The emperor built the "Ashitotsu Agari-no-Miya" (Temporary Ascending Palace) on the upper reaches of the [[Usa River]], where the siblings provided hospitality. Emperor Jimmu decreed that Usatsuhime should marry [[Ame-no-Taneko-no-Mikoto]] (ancestor of the [[Nakatomi clan]]), a union recorded in both the '''''Nihon Shoki''''' and '''''Kojiki''''', although the latter omits details about Ame-no-Taneko.
{{quote|Usa District: Usatsuhiko no Mikoto (Loyal to the Emperor, Reverent of the Gods, Upholder of Morality)
He was the son of [[Ame-no-Mikuhari-no-Mikoto]] and resided on Usa Island. He served the deity [[Hime-Okami]]. During Emperor Jimmu's eastern expedition, he built the Ashitotsu Agari-no-Miya in Usa to host the emperor. He became the ancestor of the [[Usa clan]], whose descendants include families such as the [[Miyanari]] and [[Toitsu]] baronial houses.|''Shūshinka Kyōdo Shiryō Shūsei''{{sfn|Ōita Prefecture Educational Society|1936}}}}
== Genealogy == {{See also|Usa clan}} He is described as the son of [[Ame-no-Mikuhari-no-Mikoto]], the grandson of [[Takamimusubi]].
His sister, [[Usatsuhime]], married [[Ame-no-Taneko-no-Mikoto]], becoming the mother of [[Usatsuomi-no-Mikoto]], the ancestor of the [[Nakatomi clan]].
