'''Usatsuhiko no Mikoto''' (菟狭津彦命, [[生没年不詳]]) was an ancient Japanese noble and the first {{ill|Usa Kuni no miyatsuko|ja|宇佐国造}}.

== Overview ==
In the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}}, he is referred to as '''Usatsuhiko''' (宇沙都比古), in the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}} and {{ill|Kōsonki|ja|皇孫本紀}} as '''Usatsuhiko''' (菟狭津彦), and in the {{ill|Kuni no miyatsuko honki|ja|国造本紀}} as '''Usatsuhiko no Mikoto''' (宇佐都彦命).

The {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}} describes him as residing in Usa in Toyokuni (豊国), while the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}} places him in Usa in Tsukushi (筑紫国), appearing alongside his sister {{ill|Usatsuhime no Mikoto|ja|菟狭津媛}}.

According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}}, during the {{ill|Jimmu tosei|ja|神武東征}}, Emperor Jimmu, aiming for Nakasu (present-day Yamato Province), landed in Usa, Tsukushi. There he encountered Usatsuhiko and Usatsuhime, ancestors of the {{ill|Usa Kuni no miyatsuko|ja|宇佐国造}} clan. They built a palace called Hitotsuhashi no Miya (一柱騰宮) on the upper reaches of the Usa River and hosted Emperor Jimmu. The emperor decreed that Usatsuhime be married to {{ill|Ametaneko no Mikoto|ja|天種子命}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏}}. While similar traditions are recorded in the {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀}} and {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}}, the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}} omits any mention of Ametaneko no Mikoto.

{{quote|Usa District
Usatsuhiko no Mikoto (loyalty, reverence to gods, moral principles)

A child of {{ill|Takami Musubi no Mikoto|ja|高皇産霊尊}}’s grandson {{ill|Amenokushimori no Mikoto|ja|天三降命}}, he resided on Usa Island. Serving the goddess {{ill|Hime Okami|ja|比売大神}}, he hosted Emperor Jimmu during his eastern expedition and built Hitotsuhashi no Miya to provide for him. He is regarded as the ancestor of the {{ill|Usa clan|ja|宇佐氏}}, whose descendants include notable families like the Miyase and Itozu baronial families.|{{Cite book|title=修身科郷土資料集成|author=大分県教育会|year=1936}}}}

== Genealogy ==
{{see|Usa clan}}
He is considered a child of {{ill|Amenokushimori no Mikoto|ja|天三降命}}, a descendant of {{ill|Takami Musubi no Mikoto|ja|高皇産霊尊}}.

His sister, {{ill|Usatsuhime no Mikoto|ja|菟狭津媛}}, became the wife of {{ill|Ametaneko no Mikoto|ja|天種子命}} and the mother of {{ill|Usatsumi no Mikoto|ja|宇佐津臣命}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏}}.

