According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft}}, during the {{ill|Jimmu tosei|ja|神武東征|12=draft}}, Emperor Jimmu, aiming for Nakasu (present-day Yamato Province), landed in Usa, Tsukushi. There he encountered Usatsuhiko and Usatsuhime, ancestors of the {{ill|Usa Kuni no miyatsuko|ja|宇佐国造|12=draft}} clan. They built a palace called Hitotsuhashi no Miya (一柱騰宮) on the upper reaches of the Usa River and hosted Emperor Jimmu. The emperor decreed that Usatsuhime be married to {{ill|Amenotaneko|lt=Ametaneko no Mikoto|ja|天種子命|12=draft}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏|12=draft}}. While similar traditions are recorded in the {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}} omits any mention of {{ill|Amenotaneko|lt=Ametaneko no Mikoto|ja|天種子命|12=draft}}.

