According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}}, during the {{ill|Jimmu's Eastern Expedition|lt=Jimmu's Eastern Expedition|lt=Jimmu tosei|ja|神武東征|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jimmu tosei|qq=}}, Emperor Jimmu, aiming for Nakasu (present-day Yamato Province), landed in Usa, Tsukushi. There he encountered Usatsuhiko and Usatsuhime, ancestors of the {{ill|Usa Kuni no miyatsuko|ja|宇佐国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa Kuni no miyatsuko|qq=}} clan. They built a palace called Hitotsuhashi no Miya (一柱騰宮) on the upper reaches of the Usa River and hosted Emperor Jimmu. The emperor decreed that Usatsuhime be married to {{ill|Amenotaneko|lt=Ametaneko no Mikoto|ja|天種子命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenotaneko|qq=}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatomi clan|qq=}}. While similar traditions are recorded in the {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sendai Kuji Hongi|qq=}} and {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kojiki|qq=}}, the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kojiki|qq=}} omits any mention of {{ill|Amenotaneko|lt=Ametaneko no Mikoto|ja|天種子命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenotaneko|qq=}}.

{{quote|Usa District
Usatsuhiko no Mikoto (loyalty, reverence to gods, moral principles)

A child of {{ill|Takami Musubi no Mikoto|ja|高皇産霊尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takami Musubi no Mikoto|qq=}}’s grandson {{ill|Amenokushimori no Mikoto|ja|天三降命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenokushimori no Mikoto|qq=}}, he resided on Usa Island. Serving the goddess {{ill|Hime Okami|ja|比売大神|lt=Hime-no-Ōkami|1=Himegami|3=比売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Okami|13=User:Immanuelle/Himegami|qq=}}, he hosted Emperor Jimmu during his eastern expedition and built Hitotsuhashi no Miya to provide for him. He is regarded as the ancestor of the {{ill|Usa clan|ja|宇佐氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa clan|qq=}}, whose descendants include notable families like the Miyase and Itozu baronial families.|{{Cite book|title=修身科郷土資料集成|author=大分県教育会|year=1936}}}}

== Genealogy ==
{{see|Usa clan}}
He is considered a child of {{ill|Amenokushimori no Mikoto|ja|天三降命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenokushimori no Mikoto|qq=}}, a descendant of {{ill|Takami Musubi no Mikoto|ja|高皇産霊尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takami Musubi no Mikoto|qq=}}. He was a member of the {{ill|Usa clan|ja|宇佐氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa clan|qq=}}.

His sister, {{ill|Usatsuhime no Mikoto|ja|菟狭津媛|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usatsuhime no Mikoto|qq=}}, became the wife of {{ill|Amenotaneko|lt=Ametaneko no Mikoto|ja|天種子命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenotaneko|qq=}} and the mother of {{ill|Usatsumi no Mikoto|ja|宇佐津臣命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usatsumi no Mikoto|qq=}}, the ancestor of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakatomi clan|qq=}}.

